1:1 COMMENT "# narrowing.z -- Type narrowing for union and variant types"
1:60 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# Demonstrates compile-time type narrowing via match and if predicates."
2:72 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# `x.arm` on a VALUE is always the boolean arm predicate. The payload is"
4:73 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "# reached by narrowing: inside a `case ok then { ... }` arm or the then"
5:72 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# branch of `if x.ok then`, the narrowed name IS the payload -- bare `x`"
6:73 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "# reads it directly. Reaching back through the arm name there is just a"
7:72 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# member lookup on the payload type."
8:37 EOL "\n"
